 11:33:48','2020-10-19 11:33:48','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/123819-8uRBuGwlvcu1.jpg','MC'),(2150,'Yuuki Yoshino','She is a student at Ttsuki Culinary Academy and a resident of Polar Star Dormitory. She and the other resident students from his hostel befriended with their fellow roommate Yukihira Soma and also aware to Soma\'s talent as one of the finest and unique of all. She is also a roommate and friend to her fellow student, Tadokoro Megumi and Sakaki Ryoko.  Yuki is more focus on animal meat as her main cuisine. Unlike Ikumi, the meat master in any meat culinary, Yuki often used the animal hunted game from domestic poultry to any other animals (like rabbits and deer) as her main theme. Yuki\'s cutting skill could be yet  ','2020-10-19 11:33:48','2020-10-19 11:33:48','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/n85773-n14hAePIB2tC.jpg','MC'),(2151,'Erina Nakiri','One of the two main heroines in the manga, Erina is initially the primary antagonist of Sma Yukihira, until this develops into more of a friendship. Erina is the only daughter of Azami Nakiri and an unnamed mother who is Senzaemon\'s biological daughter. Erina often detests whoever is considered \"common\" due to her regal pedigree and status within the Ttsuki organization. Her \"God Tongue\" can accurately describe the taste and composition of any food, and she gives harsh critiques to chefs and students alike. However, there have been rare occasions where she gives credit to chefs with skill. She had been promoted as the Elite Ten\'s 10th seat as a middle-schooler.\n\n~!Erina\'s \"God Tongue\" was developed years ago by Azami, through abuse and brainwashing which left her traumatized by his presence. Following this, Erina was taken in by her grandfather, Senzaemon. Despite the progress of her recovery  thanks to Jichir Saiba/Yukihira, Alice, Hisako and her uncle Natsu and aunt Leonora  Azami\'s dark influence remains a part of her. When Azami returns to replace Senzaemon as director of the academy, he again isolates Erina whose emotional condition worsens until she is nothing more than his puppet. Erina is convinced by her cousin Alice to leave the Nakiri mansion, taking shelter at the Polar Star dormitory. Erina is readily accepted by its residents, who she finds mysterious for defying her God\'s Tongue (which had never happened before) and their creative ideas. Learning that Sma is Jichir\'s son, Erina explains how Jichir was the first person able to surprise her with creative cooking. Sma is able to reproduce this effect with his eccentric chicken egg tempura, and Erina recovers.!~\n\n~!With new-found courage, Erina helped the other first-year students, preparing them for a series of matches against the chefs of Central. After several of them are expelled, Erina openly rebels against her father and resigns from the Elite Ten to directly take part in the team Shokugeki that will decide the fate of the academy.!~','2020-10-19 11:33:49','2020-10-19 11:33:49','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b75284-NprkaqPahCOU.png','MC'),(2152,'Nene Kinokuni','91st Generation student of Ttsuki Culinary Academy and the current 9th seat of the Elite Ten Council.\n\n(Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wikia)','2020-10-19 11:33:49','2020-10-19 11:33:49','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b123818-2qk9OzbVpCn6.png','SC'),(2153,'Eishi Tsukasa','Eishi is a 90th Generation student of Tootsuki Culinary Academy and the current 1st seat of the Elite Ten Council.\n\nEishi, despite being the current 1st seat of the Elite Ten Council, is quite pessimistic, feeling that he does not deserve the 1st seat. He feels exasperated by the work forced upon him as the 1st seat and the workload caused by the two Shokugekis during the 43rd Annual Tootsuki Autumn Election.\n\n(Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wikia)','2020-10-19 11:33:49','2020-10-19 11:33:49','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/121219-nhF5GmgWxnO7.jpg','SC'),(2154,'Megumi Tadokoro','__Age:__ 15\n__Family:__ Family and friends from the snowy outstation\n__Occupation:__ High School Student\n__Affiliation:__ Tootsuki Teahouse & Culinary Academy (Polar Star Dormitory)\n\nShe is one of the heroines in the manga. Originated from the snowy outstation in Japan, Megumi went to Totsuki Culinary Academy to becoming a chef and make her family proud. Unfortunately, even with her neat skills in cooking, Megumi\'s poor social skills and her extreme demophobia got the best of her and had to relied on someone who is closed to her possibly due to her humble status and her ordinary beginnings in the academy. However, after witness Soma\'s incredible cooking skills and creative method of cooking, Megumi would become his assist partner and friend through out the series.\n\nEasily nervous and sensitive, Megumi is one of the clumsy and shy students who try to doing her best while keeping her best to becoming a chef. She is easily panic whenever accidents (some are usually in a comedic fashion) happened or other students almost finish their work. She is also rather cautious student who use the words carefully to avoid unwanted consequences.It is revealed that in manga Chapter 14, Megumi is actually fear the crowd, which the crowd made her nervous even until the extent of her lacking confidence, might be the reason for her to be having barely survived passing in the academy, even with her actually good skills in cooking. With her demophobia, Megumi\'s skills were remained hindered despite her knowledge of recipe and some the cooking method. Despite her weakness, Megumi is an honest and innocent student who not lie about anything She is having a strong determination and will that will try her best to reach her dream to becoming a chef after she paired with Soma. She is also values friendship and rather observe towards any cooking style available in order for Megumi to learn the style fast (especially Soma\'s).\n\nMegumi style of cooking mostly based on cutting the ingredients using neat style. With her neat style of cutting, most of her cuts are considered as artistic as well as well prepare. It is due to her phobia to the crowd, her true nature of her cooking are often hindered . Megumi\'s careful cutting and wise using every material made her as some of the unexpected expert, even it took more weeks for her to specifying the chemistry of the ingredients for the dish. Also, despite her lack of confidence and also has phobia of crowds, Megumi\'s strong observation made her to create a dish to even supposed rivaled to Soma and other professional should she stay optimistic. With her being an assist chef beside Soma since her seemly last class at Chapple class, Megumi seemly adopted Soma\'s creativity through her observation from Soma\'s cooking.','2020-10-19 11:33:49','2020-10-19 11:33:49','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b76026-AfknPHzLCvG9.png','SC'),(2155,'Koujirou Shinomiya','Owner of a French cuisine restaurant called Shino\'s, Kojirou was a student of the 79th generation and held the first seat of the Elite Ten. He is commonly seen sporting glasses and red hair. Known as the \"Legumes Magician\", Kojirou was convinced he was going to be successful in France with his FrenchJapanese fusion restaurant, Shino\'s. However, his French staff refused to follow his recipes, even sabotaging his dishes. Facing financial ruin, he hardened himself emotionally and fired anyone who questioned his skills in the kitchen. Although this allowed him to reach the top, his proud and stubborn refusal to make exceptions resulted in his skills stagnating over the years.\n\n~!Kojirou returns to Toutsuki as a guest teacher, and \"fires\" Megumi for altering his recipe despite there being an insufficient quantity of suitable ingredients. He threatens to do the same to Souma for coming to her defense, leading Souma to challenge him to an unofficial Shokugeki. During this match, Shinomiya makes a technically perfect dish that is the unanimous winner. However, Gin gives a bonus vote for Megumi\'s dish, prompting Shinomiya to try it and admit that her flexible cooking style suits the tastes of the customer. Shinomiya is reminded of his mother\'s kindness, and taking this to heart lets Megumi pass.!~\n\n~!Kojirou reappears in the story when Souma is assigned as a stagiaire (intern) at his new restaurant, Shino\'s Tokyo. His personality has noticeably softened since their last encounter, and he helps Souma by improving the latter\'s dish which earns a place on his menu. It is revealed during this time that Kojirou chose to specialize in French cuisine in order to make his mother happy.!~\n\nShinomiya Kojirou is the main character of the Shokugeki no Soma  Etoile spinoff manga which focuses on his time in France after he graduates from Toutsuki Academy.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:49','2020-10-19 11:33:49','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/85781.jpg','MC'),(2156,'Hisako Arato','Erina\'s secretary and close friend, Hisako specializes in medicinal-based dishes. She thinks of Erina as the best, that only she could be Erina\'s number two and nobody could ever get past her to Erina\'s level. ~!She advanced to the main tournament of the Autumn Election where she was defeated by Hayama, who told her that someone who only aims to be second could never beat him. This hurt Hisako\'s pride and caused her to feel unworthy of being near Erina. While partnered with Sma for their stagiaire, Hisako reveals her insecurities but Sma convinces her otherwise and she cheers-up. They then worked together to improve their assigned restaurant with Hisako acting as the restaurant\'s auditor and business manager while Sma handled the kitchen. Hisako has since returned to Erina\'s side and become friendlier towards Sma.!~\n\n~!Hisako once read an old cooking-magazine that featured Erina\'s father, Azami, but Hisako\'s own father warned her against ever asking about Azami. When Azami returns and replaces Senzaemon as the academy\'s director, Hisako is fired as Erina\'s secretary and becomes extremely depressed. Hisako, Alice and Ry convince Erina to leave the Nakiri mansion, taking shelter inside the Polar Star Dormitory where Hisako reveals Erina\'s history. Hisako leaves Erina in their care, though she would visit every day to bring Erina a change of clothes. Hisako sought Sma as the last hope of restoring the academy, and entrusted Megumi to take care of Erina, before commencing the 3rd stage of the Promotional Exams  where Hisako was defeated by Saito and expelled.!~\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:49','2020-10-19 11:33:49','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/122708-dzXA64gVD1dq.jpg','SC'),(2157,'Ryou Kurokiba','Ryou Kurokiba is a 92nd Toutsuki Generation Student and Alice Nakiri\'s aide.\n\nGenerally lazy and gloomy, Ryou\'s personality drastically shifts once he puts on his bandana, becoming aggressive, short-tempered, and brash. He grew up in a port town in Denmark, where he became the head chef of a pub due to his commanding personality and great skill. Due to his heritage, he is an expert in seafood and he can judge the quality of any and all seafood with only a glance. Mainly seen to be beside Alice Nakiri and has known her since childhood.','2020-10-19 11:33:50','2020-10-19 11:33:50','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b88972-I6bLlOheKqkx.png','MC'),(2158,'Ryouko Sakaki','Ryko is a tall, mature-looking girl with long purple hair, orange eyes, and a large bust. She is gentle and kind, responding to the eccentrics of the other Polar Star residents in a level-headed manner and comforting the other students when they are troubled. Ryko\'s specialty is fermented foods due to her parents owning a well-known fermented-goods shop, and she maintains a workshop near the dorms to produce her own ingredients. She also keeps a bottle of \"fermented rice drink\" that she would sometimes bring out during parties and celebrations, which Sma suspects is illegally brewed sake.\n\n~!During the Autumn Elections, she presented a \"curry soy-natto rice\" using charcoal-fermented natto and homemade rice-sauce fermented with koji. The dish garnered praise from the judges, who suddenly felt as if they were in a festival due to the quintessentially Japanese and festive taste of the dish. She ultimately took 7th place in her block.!~\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:50','2020-10-19 11:33:50','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/85727.jpg','MC'),(2159,'Akira Hayama','An assistant of Professor Jun Shiomi, Akira comes from overseas; they met when he was an orphaned child and warned her about adultered spices in a market (presumably in India). Jun recognized the dormant talent in him and brought him back to Japan, where he was adopted by her teacher, Hayama. Akira quickly learned Japanese, and studied spices and aroma under Shiomi. Jun became a mother-figure for him, and his motivation to succeed at cooking stems from wanting to give something back to Jun. Akira specializes in curry dishes, with a wide knowledge of spices and aroma. He is a tall and handsome man with tanned skin and silver hair. Like Sma, he aims to be at the top of the Elite Ten. His nose is very sharp when it comes to spices, capable of identifying ingredients and grade of cooking by the first smell, considered a worthy match of Erina\'s God\'s Tongue and being identified as an \"Aroma Master\". Although Jun and Akira are both experts in spices, she uses theoretical knowledge while he depends on his sense of smell. In contrast to Jun\'s naive, ditzy, easily angered and dependent persona, Akira is mature, reliable, street smart, cool and down-to-earth.\n\n~!At the Autumn Elections, Akira had the highest score in his block, defeats Hisako in the quarter-finals, and tied with Ry in the semi-finals. This led to a three-way final with Sma, which Akira won, and showed his happiness by hugging Jun. Despite Akira\'s victory, Gin noticed some inner darknesses within Akira during the Autumn matches, warning the latter not to let his skills consume him, or else that skills cost Akira lost his desire to cook for someone\'s happiness, such as Jun\'s. Later, Alice talks Jun into using the Shiomi Seminar\'s booth during the Moon Banquet Festival, leaving Akira frustrated with Alice\'s mismanagement until they are able to settle on a proper menu.!~\n\n~!The Azami Administration disbanded the Shiomi seminar, compromised the seminar\'s business partnerships and held their research data hostage to extort Akira\'s allegiance. Compelled by his love for Jun, Akira joined the ranks of Central as a temporary 9th seat on the Elite Ten, vowing to protect the Shiomi seminar. In the Promotional Exams, Akira is ordered to defeat Sma again, and though he seems to have the upper hand, the judges note that Akira had lost the desire to cook to make someone (ie: Jun) happy, a similar warning by Gin to him back in Autumn Election. Tasting Sma\'s dish, Akira realizes what he\'d lost; Jun wishes Akira to grow independent and discover the meaning of friendship, and Akira thanks Sma for redeeming him, but is expelled for his failure and due to his time when he was being blackmailed by Central, thus unable fulfill Soma\'s offer to join Polar Star. During Regimental de Cuisine match where Akira and his friends are watching Soma and his team against Central, Akira is easily forgiven from his previous status as a blackmailed Central member, as Alice ensure as long they are actually on the same side, their bonds will never be broken.!~\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:50','2020-10-19 11:33:50','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/122706-OBGbtM9Lwt00.jpg','SC'),(2160,'Takumi Aldini','Takumi is the oldest nephew of the owner of the Trattoria Aldini, a trattoria (family-style restaurant) located in Florence, Italy. He is half-Japanese but, unlike his brother Isami, appears more European  with blond hair and blue eyes  and is noted as being extremely handsome, having fan clubs in Ttsuki Academy and his hometown. He enrolled in Ttsuki at the behest of his uncle, taking with him his mezzaluna (two-handed knife) and a bottle of homemade olive oil as a good luck charm. His specialty is Italian cuisine, although many professional chefs noted that he has a broad vision; like Sma, he will incorporate ingredients and methods from other culinary styles to create inventive dishes, and can modify his recipes while cooking. He is very kind and supportive of his less-skilled brother, to the point of risking his pride to defend Isami\'s honor.\n\nTakumi has a fierce (and somewhat one-sided) rivalry with Sma. Takumi sees Sma as someone similar to himself  both having grown-up working at small family restaurants  and a worthy rival, and jumps at any chance to compete with him. He frequently tries to challenge Sma to informal cooking challenges (usually leading to an embarrassing situation for himself), hoping to one day defeat Sma in a formal Shokugeki. Despite their rivalry, both he and Sma greatly respect each other, and likely view each other as friends outside of the arena.\n\n~!In the quarter-finals of the Autumn Elections tournament, Takumi was provoked by Mimasaka Subaru into betting his mezzaluna on their match, and lost. Sma defeats Subaru in a Shokugeki held parallel with their semi-final match and obtains the mezzaluna, but Takumi tells Sma to keep it until he can win it back. During the Moon Banquet Festival, Takumi and Isami open a booth as a branch of Trattoria Aldini, and achieve the highest sales in their area. Later, the brothers form an alliance with Sma and the other rebels against the Azami Administration. During the third stage of the Promotional Exams, Takumi and Megumi pass a simple cooking task given by Rindou, but learn from Sma and Erina that the other rebel students failed and were expelled. Takumi stands with the survivors to take part in the team Shokugeki which will decide the fate of the academy.!~\n\nTakumi and his brother Isami are the main characters of the Shokugeki no Soma  Fratelli Aldini spinoff manga which focuses on their time in Italy before going to Ttsuki Academy.','2020-10-19 11:33:50','2020-10-19 11:33:50','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b85777-hOuhNMRHyX7T.jpg','MC'),(2161,'Alice Nakiri','Alice Nakiri ( Nakiri Arisu) is a 92nd Ttsuki Generation student and Erina Nakiri\'s cousin, whose cooking style is specialized in Molecular Gastronomy. \n\nUnlike her cousin though, Alice is much more friendly and cheery. She even will talk to her rivals casually, sometimes merely to poke fun at them, something she inherited from her mother. She is also a modern girl, eager to talk about love and gossip, even with the incredibly socially dense Erina. She is also very cunning, able to manipulate Erina using reverse psychology to keep her at a local public pool despite the latter\'s initial disgust at the location. She is quite bossy with Ry, usually ordering him to do nearly everything for her. She tends to overreact when she is unhappy, throwing fits or snapping back at people. However, most of these are temporary and she will quickly return to normal in a few minutes.','2020-10-19 11:33:50','2020-10-19 11:33:50','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b88956-9eAbkC3YOql0.jpg','SC'),(2162,'Shun Ibusaki','Shun is presumably known his senior, Isshiki Satoshi better than anyone else as he was stayed much longer than the rest of the Polar Star Gang.  Unlike his passionate room mates, Shun is very realistic on the terms and very serious upon making his style in perfection. Shun is also a quiet student who prefer speak only whenever is considered as crucial by many. It is also once claimed that he is a calculative chef whose choose to act wisely over hesitation.  (Source: Wikia)','2020-10-19 11:33:50','2020-10-19 11:33:50','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/n85775-gEa0ncKXKu10.jpg','SC'),(2163,'Eizan Etsuya','He is a 91st Ttsuki Generation student of Ttsuki Culinary Academy and the current 9th Seat of the Elite Ten Council. He is known as the Alquimista aka \"The Alchemist\".','2020-10-19 11:33:51','2020-10-19 11:33:51','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b89210-OZxC3A0YXOCv.jpg','MC'),(2164,'Satoshi Isshiki','He is a student at Totsuki Culinary Academy, a resident of Polar Star Dormitory and the current 7th seat of the Elite Ten Council. Aside from that, Satoshi\'s position as one of the Elite 10 also promote a strong determination for his kouhai(junior),Yukihira Soma to drive his dream to become one of the 10 seat and could be a potential challenge for Soma due to his natural cooking abilities.   (Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wiki)','2020-10-19 11:33:51','2020-10-19 11:33:51','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/78475-DzNkdU1O9jUj.jpg','SC'),(2165,'Jouichirou Yukihira','The father of Sma Yukihira, and owner of the diner Yukihira in the Sumire Shopping District. His passion for cooking knows no bounds and his skill is world-class. As the sole parental-figure and family member in Sma\'s life, he is a mentor, teacher, and rival to his son. Like Sma, Jichir is laid-back but professional and has a serious side that emerges when he is cooking. The two share the same habit of creating horrible experimental dishes. Jichir is supportive of his son but does occasionally like to see Sma stressed and frustrated by challenging him to many cook-offs  always ending in Jichir\'s victory  to show him how much he has to grow. He left home to work abroad and sent his son to Ttsuki Academy, telling Sma that he needs to succeed in Ttsuki if he ever wants to surpass him.\n\n~! World-famous as Jichir Saiba (  Saiba Jichir), he attended Ttsuki Academy under this name, a 69th generation student, resident of the Polar Star Dorm, and 2nd seat of the Elite Ten council. Gin Dojima, the 1st seat and Jichir\'s best friend, knows that Jichir\'s cooking skills was far superior, having a record of 20 wins and 101 losses in their cooking matches. The only reason Jichir is not the 1st seat is because he is too laid back and care free.!~\n\n~! A talented and creative chef, he earned the nickname Asura (literally \'demon\') after he single handedly defeated up to 100 opponents in a regimental shokugeki. During the middle of his third year, the pressure of continuously creating new dishes took its toll on Jichiro. To the point that he skipped B.L.U.E, the world youth cooking championships, in which he was favourite to win. Gin and Senzaemon blamed themselves, and suggested Jichiro withdrew from the academy and travel the world to learn about cooking on his own terms. Azami, who was two generations behind Jichir and wanted to push Jichir\'s skills to fulfill his ideal of \"true gourmet\", was resentful when Jichir left without graduating. Eventually, Jichiro returned to Japan where he met his wife and opened a family restaurant.!~\n\n~!Jichir is a close friend of the Nakiri family, often requested by Senzaemon to privately cook for him. On one such occasion, a young Erina curiously followed the aroma of his cooking, and was allowed to join them. Jichir\'s cooking and manner inspired Erina to follow a brighter path as a chef, and this became one bright memory she held onto through Azami\'s brainwashing. Years later, Jichir arrives and coerced Azami to accept an irregular team Shokugeki, betting a lifelong servitude to Azami against Azami and his cohorts\' expulsion from the academy. Jichir, Senzaemon and Gin then act as coaches, giving special lessons to the rebel students in preparation of the upcoming team match.!~\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:52','2020-10-19 11:33:52','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/77495-81D8lngS6l3G.png','SC'),(2166,'Gin Doujima','Graduated from Tootsuki Culinary Academy, he is one of the respected legends of both his former school and Tootsuki Academy Alumni that is among the few who successfully graduated his academy with flying colors, thus became one of the proficient members of Tootsuki Resort as his graduation. As a living legend, Doujima is skillful in both culinary and board administration due to his talents in both culinary and managements that he handle the kitchen solo without the assistance of any chef around him. It is due to his professional discipline and tenacity, he is both respected and feared by many students and lecturers alike in his former academy.   As the legend by the students of the Tootsuki Culinary Academy, Doujima is believed to possesses all styles of cooking to create much unique cuisine in different way. Usually handle the kitchen solo, Doujima has no problem to make 100 different meals thanks to his vast knowledge of ingredients as well of the varieties of cuisine.   \n\n(Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wikia)','2020-10-19 11:33:52','2020-10-19 11:33:52','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/85783-pyxbOHSLvi2O.png','MC'),(2167,'Ikumi Mito','She is one of the student of Tootsuki Culinary Academy whom is also a former rival to Yukihira Soma. As the sole successor of the meat culinary expert of the Mito family for abundance knowledge about the meat culinary (especially beef and donburi), Ikumi is responsible to hold the pride of her family\'s name and like any other students in Tootsuki Culinary Academy, Ikumi is extremely prejudice upon the society classes and use high class ingredient to make a high standard dish.  It is said that Ikumi\'s rigid family rules and regulations had made her cooking skill more elegant and grace like playing piano. Using all graces of cooking by using the high grade materials as well as expensive, Ikumi can almost made the dish as elegant as it look to impressed her clients.   (Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wiki)','2020-10-19 11:33:52','2020-10-19 11:33:52','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/78935.jpg','SC'),(2168,'Subaru Mimasaka','A heavily built student who is introduced during the Autumn Election. Despite his look, he\'s smarter than he appears and has a strong sense for details. He has no specialty, but painstakingly researches and copies the chefs he faces, predicting the exact dish they will make and marginally improving upon it. He loves intense cooking-duels and totally defeating his opponent, so he always bets his opponent\'s precious tool at Shokugekis. He is a gracious host and not averse to having a casual chat with future opponents. However, before and during a match he will mock, belittle and set out to destroy his opponent.\n\n~!Subaru first appears during the Autumn Election preliminaries, taking the fourth spot from Zenji Marui and Shun Ibusaki. He insults Takumi and his brother, provoking Takumi to bet his mezzaluna, and having previously stalked Takumi and investigated his preparations, Subaru copies Takumi\'s dish with a slight improvement. Although the judges dislike his actions and methods, Subaru\'s dish is judged superior. This leads Sma to challenge Subaru to give back all 100 cooking tools he\'d won, against the total defeat of Sma quitting being a cook. Sma circumvents Subaru\'s research method by waiting until the competition starts before thinking of ways to improve his dish, something Subaru didn\'t believe was possible. After his defeat, Subaru tries to leave Ttsuki and quit as a cook but Sma convinces him to continue his studies. Subaru later appears when Sma asks for assistance at his stall during the Moon Banquet Festival. In preparation for this, Subaru went to the Yukihira diner in order to do his \"image training\", and was able to accurately copy Sma, allowing the booth to increase production and sales.!~\n\n~!During Azami\'s regime on \"Promotional Exams\", Subaru started out as neutral, until the third half where most of Soma\'s rebel friends except Takumi and Megumi are expelled, Subaru joins the rebel team led by Erina, as its 8th member during Regimental de Cuisine match as a mean to settle his debt he repaid to Sma.!~\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:52','2020-10-19 11:33:52','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/122707-eLGYAOHWfBXu.jpg','SC'),(2169,'Senzaemon Nakiri','Senzaemon is headmaster of Ttsuki Academy and Erina\'s grandfather. Known as the \"Gastric Godfather\", he has the tendency of stripping his upper body when he eats a good dish. Despite his appearance and reputation, he is reasonable and gives accurate commentary and assessment for the food he tastes without being overly critical to the losers.\n\n~!Many years previously, Senzaemon and Gin noticed Jichir Saiba\'s critical condition at the start of a tournament, and took upon themselves some of the blame for pressuring Jichir into becoming mentally trapped in the creation of his dishes. Feeling Jichir\'s talent was beyond the tasks of the academy, Senzaemon freed his former student to travel abroad and learn independently, a proposal Jichir happily accepted, as well as Gin whom Senzaemon offered him as the head of resort planner as a mean to atone their sins to ensurr no one wil share a similar fate as what happened to Joichiro before. For a period thereafter, Senzaemon hired Jichir as his private chef.!~\n\n~!Six years ago, Senzaemon exiled his son-in-law, Azami, for abusing Erina with brainwashing, and turns out even worst and dangerous to rule the academy than Joichiro\'s previous ill-fate. Senzaemon became Erina\'s legal guardian and had Azami\'s name struck from the Ttsuki records. However, in the year Erina enrolls in the academy, Azami returns and a majority of the Elite Ten vote to support Azami as headmaster, replacing Senzaemon. In the aftermath, Senzaemon revealed to Sma that he advised Jichir to have him apply to the academy. Senzaemon remains active behind-the-scenes with Jichir, working through tips from informants to wrest control from Azami.!~\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:52','2020-10-19 11:33:52','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/76028-YhCTXMKjPc6I.png','MC'),(2170,'Zenji Marui','He is a student at Totsuki Culinary Academyand a resident of Polar Star Dormitory. he and the other resident students from this hostel befriended with their fellow roommate/kouhai, Yukihira Soma whom also seen the amazing skill of the freshman. It is due to he rarely cooks, Zenji is considered as the weakest chef among the Polar Star Gang despite his brains has seemly possessed with infinite knowledge about cooking and black-&-white documents.','2020-10-19 11:33:53','2020-10-19 11:33:53','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/88721-Nee3mKUqnhIl.png','MC'),(2171,'Isami Aldini','Isami is Takumi\'s brother, and the younger nephew of the owner of Trattoria Aldini. Unlike his brother, he has more of a Japanese appearance, with black hair and sharp eyes. Isami is originally shown to be overweight, with his eyes and mouth drawn in a simple fashion, although he briefly became much thinner during the Autumn Election preliminaries. Like Isami, he enrolled in Ttsuki to hone his skills at the behest of their uncle.\n\nAlthough an equally talented chef, Isami is shown to be less sophisticated than his brother. He was scolded for trying to (and failing to) revise a dish that Takumi had made during their time in the trattoria, and constantly sought to be praised for his cooking like Takumi. Though Isami is supportive of his brother, he does aim to eventually surpass him as a cook. Nonetheless, the brothers are very close.\n\n~!At the Autumn Election, he presented a tomato-curry calzone that was praised by the judges. He aimed to surpass his brother\'s score with the dish, but ultimately finished 5th in his block. He tried to support Takumi in his quarter-finals match against Subaru Mimasaka, and was devastated when Takumi lost to his own dish. He and Takumi opened a booth during the Moon Banquet Festival, naming it a branch of Trattoria Aldini, and gained first place in sales in their area. He is targeted as a rebel by the Azami Administration\'s Promotional Exams, defeated by Eishi on the third exam and expelled.!~\n\nIsami and Takumi are featured in the Shokugeki no Soma  Fratelli Aldini spinoff manga which focuses on their time in Italy before enrolling at Ttsuki Academy.\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:53','2020-10-19 11:33:53','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/85785-ScDAk994sev0.png','MC'),(2172,'Rindou Kobayashi','She is a 90th Generation student of Tootsuki Culinary Academy and a 2nd seat of the Elite Ten Council.\n\nShe has long flowing scarlet hair that reaches down to her shoulder blades with her bangs covering her left eye. She has a lot of cat-like features, having yellow eyes with vertically slitted pupils and pronounced, cat-like teeth. She is the tallest female Elite Ten Council member.','2020-10-19 11:33:54','2020-10-19 11:33:54','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b89066-zRPZRDvbY9jD.png','MC'),(2173,'Rindou Kobayashi','She is a 90th Generation student of Tootsuki Culinary Academy and a 2nd seat of the Elite Ten Council.\n\nShe has long flowing scarlet hair that reaches down to her shoulder blades with her bangs covering her left eye. She has a lot of cat-like features, having yellow eyes with vertically slitted pupils and pronounced, cat-like teeth. She is the tallest female Elite Ten Council member.','2020-10-19 11:33:56','2020-10-19 11:33:56','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b89066-zRPZRDvbY9jD.png','SC'),(2174,'Souma Yukihira','He is the son of Jouichirou Yukihira and, until it closed, worked at his father\'s restaurant, Restaurant Yukihira. As one of the main protagonist in the manga, Soma fight his odds in the elite school to becoming the best chef in the world even with strong background discrimination of his academy. He is currently a student at Tootsuki Culinary Academy and a resident of Polar Star Dormitory.   Souma is a rather energetic child who has the constant drive to move forward with his cooking, mostly due to his rivalry with his father. Due to his drive to move forward Soma is willing to try odd things with food including \"Grilled Squid Tentacles Dressed in Peanut Butter,\" though these dishes usually don\'t go over too well. It is because the will of Soma to try to move forward, his dish often considered as creative and innovative by some peers and lecturers; lead his rivalry with all the students in the Tootsuki Culinary Academy even rough. Through all this Soma maintains a laid back attitude towards just about everything but cooking.  Soma can cook many different foods in many different styles, though he prefers what he calls \"Yukihira Style,\" which is the cooking style which he learned from his father. Soma shows an immense capability for cooking and a special adaption with learning from his mistakes and improvising through learning from said mistakes. It is due to his creativity and also resourcefulness, Soma is able to create the same dish with different ways of cooking that would create even . Unlike most student whom used lavish ingredient, Soma didn\'t care about the classes of the ingredient which claimed that neither expensive ingredients nor classy background nor fancy technique made the food better, is the wise usage and alternatives made the food interesting and the customer\'s satisfaction about the food matters. Further more, he also claimed that undefeated food in just the looks and taste in regal made him bored, which the boredom would made the chef stop improvise their food. To eliminate such boredom, Soma would continued to search different style of cooking around the world in order to improvised his cooking skills.','2020-10-19 11:33:56','2020-10-19 11:33:56','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/75216-SlBlv0myjMNc.jpg','MC'),(2175,'Terunori Kuga','__Birthday:__ May 27\n__Age:__ 17, 18-19 (Le Dessert)\n__Couisine Style:__ Chinese\n\nTerunori enrolled into Ttsuki Culinary Academy as part of the 91st Generation and would later attain the 8th seat of the Elite Ten Council. As a second year student, Terunori completed the Ttsuki Friendship and Rapport Training Camp and Stagiaire events in his first year. In his first year, he was one of the participants in the Main Tournament of the Ttsuki Autumn Election.\n\nHe is a very competitive person and he has faith in his cooking style and abilities. He has a sadist nature which is one of the reason that he prefer Sezhwan spicy recipes because he likes his customers to sweat and turn red because of the strong taste, and yet keep going at it as the taste is still appealing . He is kind of arrogant too as he is seen boasting about his position and elite 10 at times and belittling the rest of the students.\n\n~!When Senzaemon Nakiri was replaced by Azami Nakiri as the new headmaster of the academy, Terunori and three of the other Elite Ten Council members voted against the proposed change in leadership. He was boycotted the subsequent meetings and relieved in his Elite Ten\'s duties. Four months after Rebeliants\' victory, he regained a seat and has been promoted to the 3rd seat.!~ \n\n(Source: Shokugeki no Soma Wikia) ','2020-10-19 11:33:56','2020-10-19 11:33:56','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b123820-BLIl2ZwHi1zh.jpg','SC'),(2176,'Eishi Tsukasa','Eishi is a 90th Generation student of Tootsuki Culinary Academy and the current 1st seat of the Elite Ten Council.\n\nEishi, despite being the current 1st seat of the Elite Ten Council, is quite pessimistic, feeling that he does not deserve the 1st seat. He feels exasperated by the work forced upon him as the 1st seat and the workload caused by the two Shokugekis during the 43rd Annual Tootsuki Autumn Election.\n\n(Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wikia)','2020-10-19 11:33:56','2020-10-19 11:33:56','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/121219-nhF5GmgWxnO7.jpg','MC'),(2177,'Erina Nakiri','One of the two main heroines in the manga, Erina is initially the primary antagonist of Sma Yukihira, until this develops into more of a friendship. Erina is the only daughter of Azami Nakiri and an unnamed mother who is Senzaemon\'s biological daughter. Erina often detests whoever is considered \"common\" due to her regal pedigree and status within the Ttsuki organization. Her \"God Tongue\" can accurately describe the taste and composition of any food, and she gives harsh critiques to chefs and students alike. However, there have been rare occasions where she gives credit to chefs with skill. She had been promoted as the Elite Ten\'s 10th seat as a middle-schooler.\n\n~!Erina\'s \"God Tongue\" was developed years ago by Azami, through abuse and brainwashing which left her traumatized by his presence. Following this, Erina was taken in by her grandfather, Senzaemon. Despite the progress of her recovery  thanks to Jichir Saiba/Yukihira, Alice, Hisako and her uncle Natsu and aunt Leonora  Azami\'s dark influence remains a part of her. When Azami returns to replace Senzaemon as director of the academy, he again isolates Erina whose emotional condition worsens until she is nothing more than his puppet. Erina is convinced by her cousin Alice to leave the Nakiri mansion, taking shelter at the Polar Star dormitory. Erina is readily accepted by its residents, who she finds mysterious for defying her God\'s Tongue (which had never happened before) and their creative ideas. Learning that Sma is Jichir\'s son, Erina explains how Jichir was the first person able to surprise her with creative cooking. Sma is able to reproduce this effect with his eccentric chicken egg tempura, and Erina recovers.!~\n\n~!With new-found courage, Erina helped the other first-year students, preparing them for a series of matches against the chefs of Central. After several of them are expelled, Erina openly rebels against her father and resigns from the Elite Ten to directly take part in the team Shokugeki that will decide the fate of the academy.!~','2020-10-19 11:33:56','2020-10-19 11:33:56','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b75284-NprkaqPahCOU.png','SC'),(2178,'Satoshi Isshiki','He is a student at Totsuki Culinary Academy, a resident of Polar Star Dormitory and the current 7th seat of the Elite Ten Council. Aside from that, Satoshi\'s position as one of the Elite 10 also promote a strong determination for his kouhai(junior),Yukihira Soma to drive his dream to become one of the 10 seat and could be a potential challenge for Soma due to his natural cooking abilities.   (Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wiki)','2020-10-19 11:33:56','2020-10-19 11:33:56','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/78475-DzNkdU1O9jUj.jpg','SC'),(2179,'Nene Kinokuni','91st Generation student of Ttsuki Culinary Academy and the current 9th seat of the Elite Ten Council.\n\n(Source: Shokugeki no Souma Wikia)','2020-10-19 11:33:57','2020-10-19 11:33:57','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b123818-2qk9OzbVpCn6.png','MC'),(2180,'Alice Nakiri','Alice Nakiri ( Nakiri Arisu) is a 92nd Ttsuki Generation student and Erina Nakiri\'s cousin, whose cooking style is specialized in Molecular Gastronomy. \n\nUnlike her cousin though, Alice is much more friendly and cheery. She even will talk to her rivals casually, sometimes merely to poke fun at them, something she inherited from her mother. She is also a modern girl, eager to talk about love and gossip, even with the incredibly socially dense Erina. She is also very cunning, able to manipulate Erina using reverse psychology to keep her at a local public pool despite the latter\'s initial disgust at the location. She is quite bossy with Ry, usually ordering him to do nearly everything for her. She tends to overreact when she is unhappy, throwing fits or snapping back at people. However, most of these are temporary and she will quickly return to normal in a few minutes.','2020-10-19 11:33:57','2020-10-19 11:33:57','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b88956-9eAbkC3YOql0.jpg','MC'),(2181,'Miyoko Houjou','A 92nd Totsuki Generation student. She is also the heiress to her family restaurant.','2020-10-19 11:33:58','2020-10-19 11:33:58','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/b162355-yP5IxImiIt21.png','SC'),(2182,'Ryouko Sakaki','Ryko is a tall, mature-looking girl with long purple hair, orange eyes, and a large bust. She is gentle and kind, responding to the eccentrics of the other Polar Star residents in a level-headed manner and comforting the other students when they are troubled. Ryko\'s specialty is fermented foods due to her parents owning a well-known fermented-goods shop, and she maintains a workshop near the dorms to produce her own ingredients. She also keeps a bottle of \"fermented rice drink\" that she would sometimes bring out during parties and celebrations, which Sma suspects is illegally brewed sake.\n\n~!During the Autumn Elections, she presented a \"curry soy-natto rice\" using charcoal-fermented natto and homemade rice-sauce fermented with koji. The dish garnered praise from the judges, who suddenly felt as if they were in a festival due to the quintessentially Japanese and festive taste of the dish. She ultimately took 7th place in her block.!~\n\n(Source: Wikipedia)','2020-10-19 11:33:58','2020-10-19 11:33:58','https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/character/large/85727.jpg','MC'),(2183,'Jouichirou Yukihira','The father of Sma Yukihira, and owner of the diner Yukihira in the Sumire Shopping District. His passion for cooking knows no bounds and his skill is world-class. As the sole parental-figure and family member in Sma\'s life, he is a mentor, teacher, and rival to his son. Like Sma, Jichir is laid-back but professional and has a serious side that emerges when he is cooking. The two share the same habit of creating